FBIS4-34855 "drlat123_a_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Canadian Company Announces Joint Mining Venture Canadian Company Announces Joint Mining Venture FL2506155494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 24 Jun 94 FL2506155494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [From the "Exclusive" program] [Text] In Toronto, the Canadian (Cherris) Company has announced that it will create a joint enterprise with Cuban Nickel Enterprise for mining nickel and cobalt in Cuba. The new enterprise includes others that will be directly in charge of the extraction, refining, and global marketing of nickel and cobalt. The Cuban Government has granted the new entity a mining claim comprising more than 60 million tons of iron oxide ore with nickel, with an 80 percent concentration of the reserves tested.
